{"id":691,"date":"2008-09-03T09:14:35","date_gmt":"2008-09-03T14:14:35","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/badass_pony.php"},"modified":"2008-09-03T09:14:35","modified_gmt":"2008-09-03T14:14:35","slug":"badass_pony","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/badass_pony.php","title":{"rendered":"Badass Pony"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/ford_mustang_badge.jpg\" alt=\"Ford Mustang Badge, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I don&#8217;t know much about cars, or what makes a good car good, and I haven&#8217;t owned one in five years, but somehow I know that Ford Mustangs kick ass. Or at least they appear to. Regardless&hellip; as Ford prepares for the launch of the 2010 edition of the Mustang they have issued a <a href=\"http:\/\/media.ford.com\/newsroom\/release_display.cfm?release=28950\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">press release for the redesign of the badge<\/a>. Fitting somewhere between logo design and sculpture, this new pony comes with some of the most awesome (and I strangely mean this without sarcasm) press releasing: <em>It&#8217;s just a faster-looking steed.<\/em> &rarr; <em>We lifted the head to make the pony more proud, tipped the neck into the wind to give it a feeling of greater speed and better balance.<\/em> &rarr; <em>It&#8217;s more chiseled and more defined and looks more like a wild horse<\/em>. And indeed it is! It really looks like it could do even more ass kicking than the previous version. The differences are hard to discern so I quickly put <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/ford_mustang_badge_overlay.php\" onclick=\"window.open('https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/ford_mustang_badge_overlay.php','popup','width=369,height=165,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false\">this overlay together (yellow is the new badge)<\/a>. I love it when companies obsess over details to make a stronger visual, reminds me a little of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/random\/nyt-moma-article.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Matthew Carter&#8217;s redrawing of the MoMA logo<\/a>. Giddy up!<\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphicology.com\/blog\/2008\/8\/28\/192-new-ford-mustang.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jason who already reported it on his blog<\/a> for the tip.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[59,9,26],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/691"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=691"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/691\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=691"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/